	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Will adding another ~2 feet of wiring in between a NES/Famicom cart slot and the motherboard introduce a delay large enough to make the system unusable?  Should I be concerned about the resistance of the wires?  
<br />I'm still working on that PC10 adapter.  (finally got my arcade machine, have the pinouts all done, just trying to figure out where to mount the adapter before I make my prototype.)

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


	<hr width="85%" />

