	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I found a page which lists <a href="http://www.adaptec.com/worldwide/support/supporteditorial.jsp?sess=no&amp;language=English+US&amp;prodkey=SCSI_glossary#adt" class="postlink">1.6ns signal propagation delay per foot</a>, double that for round-trip. I don't know a lot about termination but <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reflection_%28electrical%29" class="postlink">signal reflection</a> might be an issue. It'll also make a nice RF noise source if it's unshielded :).

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


